				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$n = \frac{{{\mathrm{I}}_{\mathrm{x}}{\mathrm{B}}_{\mathrm{z}}}}{{V_{\mathrm{H}}te}}$$\end{document}where Ix and Bz is applied constant current and magnetic field, respectively. VH is measured Hall voltage. t is the thickness of the sample and e is elementary charge.
